.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-1-13::.
City: miami, venice, boston, new-york, rome, san-francisco
The people use 6 different means of transport: car, motorbike, roller, scooter, tram, trike
1. the person traveling to new-york is the person driving the roller##1
2. the person traveling to miami is on the left of the person traveling to san-francisco##1
3. the person driving the roller is on the left of the person traveling to miami##1
4. the person traveling to miami is the person driving the motorbike##1
5. the person traveling to venice is on the right of the person driving the car##1
6. the person driving the scooter is on the right of the person traveling to venice##1
7. the person traveling to boston is on the left of the person driving the tram##1
8. the person driving the car is on the far left##1
9. the person traveling to san-francisco is the person driving the trike##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |   1   |     2     |       3        |     4     |     5     |   6    |
| City         | boston | venice | rome | new-york | miami    | san-francisco |
| Transport   | car   | tram      | scooter        | roller    | motorbike | trike  |

